{{Infobox civilian attack | title = March 2016 Diyarbakır bombing | partof = [[Kurdish–Turkish conflict (2015–present)]] | image = File:Diyarbakir in Turkey.svg | caption = Location of Diyarbakır Province in Turkey | location = [[Diyarbakır]], [[Turkey]] | target = | coordinates = | date = 31 March 2016 | time = | timezone = | type = [[Car bombing]] | fatalities = 7 | injuries = 27 | perps = | perpetrator = [[PKK]]<ref>http://www.dw.com/tr/diyarbak%C4%B1r-sald%C4%B1r%C4%B1s%C4%B1n%C4%B1-pkk-%C3%BCstlendi/a-19158776</ref> | weapons = | motive = }} {{Campaignbox PKK–Turkey conflict}}
A car bomb, targeting an armored vehicle transporting police personnel, exploded close to a bus terminal in the Bağlar district of Diyarbakır, Turkey, killing at least seven police officers and wounding 27 more people, including 13 officers, according to a joint statement by Turkish officials and the police. The attack comes one day before Turkish Prime Minister Ahmet Davutoğlu's scheduled visit to the city. There has been no claim of responsibility. CNN points out both Kurdish rebels and ISIL militants have claimed similar recent incidents.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2016/03/loud-explosion-rocks-turkey-diyarbakir-160331142831391.html|title=Car bomb kills police in Turkey's Diyarbakir|publisher=|accessdate=16 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/middle_east/explosion-reported-in-turkeys-diyarbakir-4-deaths-reported/2016/03/31/104ed32c-f754-11e5-958d-d038dac6e718_story.html|title=Sorry, we can’t seem to find the page you’re looking for.|date=31 March 2016|publisher=|accessdate=28 June 2016|via=washingtonpost.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2016/04/01/world/europe/turkey-diyarbakir-bomb.html|title=Car Bomb Kills 7 Turkish Police Officers in Diyarbakir|date=1 April 2016|work=The New York Times|accessdate=16 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-turkey-blast-idUKKCN0WX1XP|title=Car bomb kills seven police in Turkey's Diyarbakir - officials|author=Orhan Coskun and Seyhmus Cakan|date=31 March 2016|work=Reuters UK|accessdate=16 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2016/03/31/europe/turkey-violence/|title=7 police killed in Diyarbakir, Turkey, bombing - CNN.com|author=Greg Botelho and Gul Tuysuz, CNN|date=31 March 2016|work=CNN|accessdate=16 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-35937596|title=Turkey Diyarbakir: Bomb kills police in south-eastern city|work=BBC News|accessdate=16 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailysabah.com/nation/2016/03/31/7-officers-killed-27-wounded-in-diyarbakir-terror-attack-on-police-vehicle-in-southeastern-turkey|title=7 officers killed, 27 wounded in Diyarbakır terror attack on police vehicle in southeastern Turkey|date=31 March 2016|work=DailySabah|accessdate=16 April 2016}}</ref>
